            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Down Beckenham Kent,</placeName>
                        <date>October 26th 1871.</date>
                        <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I am much obliged for your kind and interesting letter […]<ref target="#foot.f1"/> what you say about the men of the Seychelles islands is quite new to me.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> The case seems nearly parallel, though of a reverse nature, with that of the difference in stature between the inhabitants of the lofty volcanic and low coral islets of the Pacific.</p>
                        <p>With my thanks. | I remain, Dear Sir, | Yours very faithfully, | C<hi rend="smallCaps">h</hi>. D<hi rend="smallCaps">arwin</hi>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                
                
                
            </div>
            
            
            
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">Ellipses are in the original printed text.</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f2">Bouton had written about the immense strength and vigour of the men of the Seychelles (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 19, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7961.xml">letter from Louis Bouton, 22 September 1871</ref>).</note>
            </div>
        
